content:
Hi all. I'm seeing a new error when building my IG following release of the latest publisher (v1.1.60). It is being reported an all Bundle and Parameters profiles in the guide. The error is "[element] has no assigned types". When I hover over the error in qa.html, "SD_NO_TYPES" is shown.

Examples...

  • The element Bundle.entry.link has no assigned types
  • The element Parameters.parameter.part has no assigned types

The errors are being reported in cases where the named element is part of the profile's differential... and also when it is not. As an example, none of the Parameters profiles throwing this error include Parameters.parameter.part, which is an optional element.

Is anyone else seeing this?
I could send you one of the profiles that's causing the error...
can you commit the IG to a branch?

I published the IG to build.fhir.org. Here's the QA.html. Just let me know if I should do anything else
http://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/fhir-specialty-rx/branches/master/qa.html
